==English==
===Etymology===
*From the [[Japanese]] 津波 (tsunami), "[[harbour]] [[wave]]".

===Noun===
'''tsunami''' (''plural'' '''tsunamis''')
*A very large [[wave]], caused by an [[undersea]] [[earthquake]], that often causes colossal damage when it reaches land.

====Synonyms====
*[[tidal wave]] (''technically incorrect'')

====Translations====
*Japanese: [[津波]] (つなみ, tsunami)

